    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt's currently impossible to get information about the selected code action using `vim.lsp.buf.code_action`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhy would that be useful? \nIt would allow us to play around with code actions, for example: get the last code action context and apply the same code action to all diagnostics with the same context in the current workspace, or get the last code action edits and reuse it by implementing it as a dot repeat.\n\n---\n\nRelated: #28004",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
